    },
    {
      "id": "line-002",
      "start": 7.8,
      "end": 14.98,
      "text": "For more information or to volunteer, please visit libravox.org.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-003",
      "start": 15.62,
      "end": 20.08,
      "text": "Recorded by Duncan, also known as Nerdvana.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-004",
      "start": 20.72,
      "end": 22.48,
      "text": "And his son Andrew.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-005",
      "start": 23.66,
      "end": 25.42,
      "text": "In the known as Assa, Florida.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-006",
      "start": 26.52,
      "end": 27.86,
      "text": "Asip's fables.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-007",
      "start": 28.78,
      "end": 30.68,
      "text": "Father and sons.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-008",
      "start": 32.4,
      "end": 38.14,
      "text": "A certain man had several sons who were always crawling with one another.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-009",
      "start": 38.86,
      "end": 40.44,
      "text": "And try as he might.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-010",
      "start": 41.38,
      "end": 44.66,
      "text": "He could not get them to live together in harmony.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-011",
      "start": 46.0,
      "end": 50.9,
      "text": "So he determined to convince them of their folly by the following means.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-012",
      "start": 52.68,
      "end": 55.14,
      "text": "Bingham fetched the bundle of sticks.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-013",
      "start": 55.72,
      "end": 59.6,
      "text": "He invited each intern to break it across his knee.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-014",
      "start": 61.16,
      "end": 63.4,
      "text": "All tried and all failed.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-015",
      "start": 64.42,
      "end": 66.44,
      "text": "And then he undid the bundle.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-016",
      "start": 66.96,
      "end": 70.56,
      "text": "And handed them the sticks one by one.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-017",
      "start": 70.82,
      "end": 73.72,
      "text": "When they had no difficulty at all, it raked them.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-018",
      "start": 74.68,
      "end": 76.16,
      "text": "There, my boys.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-019",
      "start": 77.36,
      "end": 78.12,
      "text": "Said he.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-020",
      "start": 79.16,
      "end": 83.42,
      "text": "United, you will be more than a match for your enemies.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-021",
      "start": 84.6,
      "end": 92.44,
      "text": "But if you quarrel and separate, your weakness will put you at the mercy of those who attack you.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-022",
      "start": 94.06,
      "end": 96.1,
      "text": "Union is strength.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-023",
      "start": 98.28,
      "end": 102.38,
      "text": "End of father and sons.",
      "note": ""
    }
  ],
